Calls for intensified international cooperation, including by fully implementing the International Health Regulations (2005),
World Health Organization, document WHA58/2005/REC/1, resolution 58.3, annex. to contain, mitigate and defeat the COVID-19 pandemic, including by exchanging information, scientific knowledge and best practices and by applying the relevant guidelines recommended by the World Health Organization, and by participating in and supporting ongoing discussions to draft and negotiate a World Health Organization convention, agreement or other international instrument on pandemic prevention, preparedness and response, with a view to adoption under article 19 or under other provisions of the Constitution of the World Health Organization
United Nations, Treaty Series, vol. 14, No. 221. as may be deemed appropriate by the intergovernmental negotiating body and through discussions on strengthening the implementation of and compliance with the International Health Regulations (2005);
